==Colonies and Outposts ==

===The Diner Group ===
A group consists of several travelers who remain at this level; however, their total number is never consistent due to wanderers joining and departing the group. The crew settles into a couple of restaurants that link each other and establish their eateries, serving various cuisines that are typically famous Southeast Asia meals. The group regularly welcomes newcomers as considerable participants are close friends and have chosen to stay inside the level for an ample duration. Every month, the group base's food and other supplies come in via the door that connects to [[Level 33]].
==Entrances and Exits ==
===Entrances ===
* Entering yellow color doors in [[Level 33]] may lead to this level;
* Pressing the buttons "9" and "8" on the vending machine in the break room of [[Level 16]] will transport one to this level;
* Entering a metallic door sometimes found in The Ballrooms of [[Level 5]] will lead one to this level;
* Within some accessible skyscrapers in [[Level 97]], one might find a long deep, specific staircase going downwards with signs pointing to a "Dining Area", leading to the interior of a restaurant here after descending for long enough. This same staircase cannot be used to re-enter [[Level 97]], as it will turn into a normal staircase leading to any upper floor, part or area of a restaurant in this level;
* A set of wooden diner doors in [[Level 7.5]] will lead one here.
===Exits ===
* One can use the same entrance gate to [[Level 33]];
* Few individuals allege to have entered [[Level 6]] by stepping down the dark alleyway between the buildings;
* Noclipping will lead one to [[Level 99]];
* Entering a marine-themed restaurant labelled "Atlantis Restaurant" will lead one to [[Level 88]];
* Entering a dark, indoor hallway sends one to [[Level 570]].
